    "causal_summary": "system-deep-loop is the single public skill that merges active deep-loop persona modes (deep-research, deep-review, deep-ai-council, deep-improvement, deep-alignment) into one advisor identity with active mode packets, routed by workflowMode through mode-registry.json over a nested runtime/ infrastructure layer (frozen, MCP-free; formerly the separate deep-loop-runtime skill, merged 2026-07-08). @context owns one-shot retrieval while research and review carry bounded context snapshots; alignment performs read-only-by-default conformance audits against named standard authorities. Per-mode convergence, state, artifacts, and tool-permission contracts are preserved unflattened; the three-tier discriminator (workflowMode / runtimeLoopType / backendKind) keeps graph-backed modes, improvement-host modes, and the alignment packet's runtime-loop contract distinct. The prior deep-loop-workflows <-> deep-loop-runtime inter-skill relationship is now intra-skill structure; runtime/ has no graph-metadata.json of its own and is not independently advisor-routable.",
